  "text": "The idea of flux limiters can be illustrated by computation of the flux F 0,1 of the conserved quantity u between a cell marked by 0 and one of two its neighbour cells marked by ±1: Many flux limiter schemes have been invented during the last two decades [CITATION_1] . No particular limiter works well for all problems, and a choice is usually made on a trial and error basis.",
